Results
A 10μg/m3 increase in PM2.5 exposure was associated with a small elevated risk of hypertension (adjusted odds ratio (OR) 1.05, 95% confidence interval (CI) 1.00–1.10) risk of heart disease (1.08 95% CI 1.00–1.16). The association between PM2.5 and hypertension was found in non-Hispanic white adults (OR 1.10 95% CI 1.04–1.17) but not in non-Hispanic black or Hispanic adults.
